data.name: Crispy Orange Chicken
data.quickTastyDescription: A deliciously crispy chicken coated in a tangy orange sauce, perfect for a quick and satisfying meal!
detailedCookingInstructions: Cut the chicken breast into bite-sized pieces and season with salt and pepper.
In a bowl, beat the egg and then mix in the cornstarch until well combined.
Heat the vegetable oil in a large pan over medium-high heat.
Dip each chicken piece into the egg mixture, then carefully place it in the hot oil.
Fry the chicken for about 5-7 minutes, or until golden and crispy. Remove and drain on paper towels.
In a separate saucepan, combine the orange juice, soy sauce, brown sugar, garlic, and ginger. Bring to a simmer and let cook for 5 minutes until slightly thickened.
Add the crispy chicken to the sauce and toss to coat evenly.
Serve topped with sliced green onions and sesame seeds.
data.detailedName: Crispy Orange Chicken with Tangy Sauce
